# 3. 大切なもの

Toya: “Good morning.”
Male Student A: “No!! I'm done for...!!”
Male Student B: “Give up already, will you...?”
Toya: “Morning. Did something happen?”
Male Student A: “You're not gonna believe this, Toya! I got a horrible score on that test for music class...”
Male Student B: “He's been asked to sing in front of the entire class, and he has to improve his music skills before then.”
Male Student A: “How am I supposed to do that?! I'm totally tone deaf!”
Male Student B: “But you have to do this... Oh, wait.”
Male Student B: “Why don't you ask Toya for some tips? If I recall, he always gets amazing grades in music.”
Toya: “What...?”
Male Student A: “Hey, that's right! You got any good advice for me, Toya?!”
Toya: “Well... First, if you wish to improve your pitch...”
Toya: “...but those are the only remedies that come to mind. I only hope that some of that was helpful.”
Male Students: “...”
Male Student A: “That's amazing, Toya! You're a total pro!”
Male Student B: “Yeah. I'd heard that you used to be a pretty serious musician, but you're more knowledgeable than I even imagined.”
Toya: “I'm really nothing special. And I've quit playing music.”
Male Student A: “Really? Seems like a waste.”
Male Student B: “I know, right? Now I really wanna hear you sing, Toya.”
Male Student B: “Do you have any plans to give it another go?”
Toya: “No... I don't think I will.”
Male Student A: “Really...? Oh, did something bad happen?”
Male Student B: “Hey, you're being way too nosy.”
Toya: “No, it's okay.”
Toya: “Nothing bad happened per se. It just wasn't for me. That's all.”
Toya: “Yes, things were hard at times, but...”
Toya: “My memories of that time all feel like a dream now.”
Toya: “They have a brilliance to them.”
Toya: “They're precious and unforgettable.”
Male Student A: “We had no idea... Also, you seem to really enjoy talking about all that.”
Male Student A: “I feel like you should give it another try.”
Toya: (A message? From who...? Oh, it's some of my old classmates from Kamiyama High.)
Toya: (Let's see what it says...)
Toya: ...!
Toya: (I wasn't expecting a message like that.)
Toya: (They invited me to a get-together for old time's sake.)
Toya: (Meeting them does sound like fun...)
Toya: (But what do I do...? I came all the way back without sending a reply.)
Toya: (I can't let this drag on forever...)
Natsuomi: I see you're home, Toya.
Toya: ...! Natsuomi... I didn't realize you were home...
Natsuomi: Yes, I'm back. Did anything happen while I was gone?
Toya: Nothing to report. And congratulations on your concert. I'll get dinner ready now.
Natsuomi: No, I'll cook tonight. It's been a while since I last did.
Toya: Oh, then... I'll set the table.
Natsuomi: Okay, thank you.
Toya: This is good. You really are a much better cook than me.
Natsuomi: To be fair, I can't make anything all that fancy.
Natsuomi: How has school been lately?
Toya: Fun. But I can't let my guard down because of all the tests they've been giving us.
Natsuomi: As long as you pay attention during class each day, you should be able to achieve good results. But it's also important to read ahead and review what you've already covered.
Toya: Yes, I'll do that...
Toya: ...
Natsuomi: ...
Natsuomi: You seem rather despondent. Did something happen?
Toya: Oh...
Natsuomi: If there's something on your mind, then I'll be more than happy to listen.
Toya: My friends from Japan contacted me.
Toya: We were classmates when we were first-years, and they invited me to gather with them for old time's sake. It'd be nice to go, but...
Natsuomi: Then, you should go. What's holding you back?
Toya: I know. But the thing is...
Toya: I'm not sure if I should.
Natsuomi: What do you mean?
Toya: ...
Toya: I'm worried that my old street-music teammate is also going to be there.
Toya: I didn't fully commit the way he needed me to, which ended up hurting him...
Toya: Which is why...
Toya: I doubt he'll want to see my face.
Natsuomi: I see...
Natsuomi: Do you dislike him now, Toya?
Toya: Huh...?
Natsuomi: You just said that he probably wouldn't want to see you.
Natsuomi: So, do you feel the same way about him?
Toya: ...! No, I don't.
Toya: But I feel too ashamed to show my face.
Toya: At the same time, I...
Toya: I'm...very grateful for him.
Toya: Because he taught me just how much fun singing can be.
Natsuomi: ...
Natsuomi: Then, you should go.
Toya: What...?
Natsuomi: I understand why you feel conflicted.
Natsuomi: However, you both love music and were working towards the same goal. So, I believe you'll be able to find some common ground.
Toya: But...
Natsuomi: Also, the look on your face just now is all the more reason why you should tell him how you feel.
Natsuomi: That was the look of someone who cares deeply about something.
Toya: ...
Natsuomi: This is all the advice I can give you. My hope is that you don't regret any decisions you make...
Toya: (I...)
